// Package assets owns the Githome web front's built static assets: the
// content-hashed CSS and JS bundles, the manifest that maps a logical name to
// its hashed file, and the Octicon-equivalent icon registry the render layer
// inlines. The bundles are produced by the build command in ./build and embedded
// here; nothing in this package imports the web front or the persistence layer.
// See implementation/01 and implementation/04.
package assets

// Icons is the Octicon-equivalent registry: a map from icon name to the inner
// SVG body (the path markup) drawn on a 16x16 viewBox. The render layer's octicon
// helper wraps a lookup in the outer <svg> with the size and accessibility
// attributes; an unknown name renders a visible placeholder, never the input, so
// a typo is caught in review rather than shipped (see implementation/04 section 8
// and implementation/03 section 4). The path data is authored from scratch to
// match the rendered glyph; no @primer/octicons package is vendored.
//
